    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hydrometers for the determination of the alcoholic content expressed in Gay-Lussac degrees. The device was invented by French physicist and chemist Louis Gay-Lussac. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
